ProcessFlowMigration.name: ProcessFlowMigration
ProcessFlowMigration.description: Represents a process's migrated criteria and the resulting migrated flow.

DestinationFlowDefinitionId.description: The ID of the resulting migrated flow.

DestinationFlowVersionId.description: The version ID of the migrated flow.

DeveloperName.description: The unique name of the object in the API. This name can contain only underscores and alphanumeric characters, and must be unique in your org. It must begin with a letter, not include spaces, not end with an underscore, and not contain two consecutive underscores.

ManageableState.description: Indicates the manageable state of the specified component that is contained in a package.

MigratedCriteriaLabel.description: The label of the criteria that was migrated.

MigratedCriteriaName.description: The name of the criteria that was migrated.

NamespacePrefix.description: The namespace of the package containing the process flow migration object.

ProcessVersionId.description: The version ID of the originating process.
